      • give

        public void give(me.taylorkelly.mywarp.Actor actor,
                 boolean giveDirectly,
                 boolean ignoreLimits,
                 me.taylorkelly.mywarp.util.profile.Profile receiver,
                 me.taylorkelly.mywarp.warp.Warp warp)
          throws com.sk89q.intake.CommandException,
                 com.sk89q.intake.util.auth.AuthorizationException,
                 PlayerBinding.NoSuchPlayerException,
                 ExceedsLimitException
        Changes the owner of a Warp.
        Parameters:
        actor - the Actor
        giveDirectly - whether the Warp should be given directly, without asking the owner for acceptance
        ignoreLimits - whether the limits of the new owner should be ignored
        receiver - the Profile of the player who should receive the Warp
        warp - the Warp
        Throws:
        com.sk89q.intake.CommandException - if the warp is owned by the receiver
        com.sk89q.intake.util.auth.AuthorizationException - if the Actor does have enough permissions
        PlayerBinding.NoSuchPlayerException - if the receiver is offline and the flags to bypass this check where not given
        ExceedsLimitException - if the limits of the receiver would be exceeded

               throws com.sk89q.intake.CommandException,
                      com.sk89q.intake.util.auth.AuthorizationException,
                      PlayerBinding.NoSuchPlayerException,
                      ExceedsInitiatorLimitException,
                      ExceedsLimitException
        Privatizes a Warp.
        Parameters:
        actor - the Actor
        ignoreLimits - whether the limits of the owner should be ignored
        warp - the warp
        Throws:
        com.sk89q.intake.CommandException - if the Warp is already private
        com.sk89q.intake.util.auth.AuthorizationException - if ignoreLimits is true, but the given Actor does not have the required permission
        PlayerBinding.NoSuchPlayerException - if the warp's creator is offline and ignoreLimits is false
        ExceedsInitiatorLimitException - if the limit of the Actor would be exceeded by privatizing the warp and ignoreLimits is false
        ExceedsLimitException - if a Limit would be exceeded by privatizing the warp and ignoreLimits is false
